article.headline: James Madison 65, Navy 60
article.story: HARRISONBURG, Va. (AP) -- Ray Barbosa scored 21 points, including four free throws in the final 1:40, as James Madison defeated Navy 65-60 Sunday. Barbosa hit all three free throws after being fouled on a 3-point attempt with 1:40 remaining to put James Madison (2-1) ahead to stay, 61-60. He added a foul shot for the game's final point with 10 seconds left. The Dukes led by 12 points twice -- first on Barbosa's 3-pointer with 4:09 left in the first half, and later on a Barbosa layup to make it 38-26 with 13:53 remaining -- before Navy (0-4) rallied. David Hooper scored eight of his 20 points in a 21-4 Navy run. A Jeff Charles layup tied the game at 42, Taj Mathews hit a 3-pointer to give the Midshipmen their first lead, and a tip-in by Charles made it 47-42 with 9:16 remaining. The Dukes regained the lead 51-49 on Chris Cathlin's layup with 6:44 remaining. A layup by George O'Garro and a free throw by Charles put Navy back on top 52-51 with 5:05 left, and the Midshipmen maintained the lead until Charles' foul sent Barbosa to the line to shoot three. James Madison was 19-of-29 from the free-throw line while Navy was just 3-of-6. Cathlin finished with 14 points for James Madison. Charles had 19 points and 12 rebounds for the Midshipmen, and Laramie Mergerson came off the bench to score 10 points.
